review_blob: Delicious malty aroma of dark fruits with a hint of chocolate. Can smell the alcohol a bit as well. Taste is delicious dark fruity malt - taste reminds me of a doppelbock as the Belgian yeast doesnt seem to be as present as other Belgians Ive tried. Bit of alcohol in the flavour as well. One of the easiest drinking and well-balanced Belgian ales Ive had!

Growler from brewery. This wildcard is an blend of falconers flight, Polaris, and orange peel. Aroma is pronounced citrus with a hint of earthiness which I assume comes from the Polaris hops. Taste is quite good -  light malts with a pronounced citrus flavour. Mouth feel is spot on for an APA. A Tasty summer beer -  will try again in its next iteration.
Nothing good or bad about this beer -  taste is almost neutral. Light biscuits with a faint hop taste in the finish. Not a bad summer beer but rather uninteresting.

Finally got to try this.  Aroma is fruity and some cloves reminiscent of Unibroues Maudite.  Taste is... Interesting. Spicy, fruity, even a bit medicinal. As I take a few more sips the taste really develops its surprisingly complex for such a light beer. Aftertaste is exceptional and as I tease it around the palate I notice all kinds of flavors: flaked wheat, banana, even some fresh grass presumably from the hops.  Delightful

Cloudy light amber appearance. Aroma is quite hoppy - citrus and pine with a hint of caramel as well. Carbonation is light but perfect for this style in my opinion the mouthfeel is also bang on with the right amount of oily-ness. Taste is quite hoppy a lot of pine and kind of skunky as well. The bitter and citrus flavours take over towards the end. The malts are quite balanced and suit the hops well they didnt go overboard on the caramel like some IPA/DIPAs.

500ml bottle from LCBO. Poured cool into a tulip glass. Colour is a clear vibrant orange. Aroma is fruity and reminiscent of american IPAs. Taste is impressive - kiwis most pronounced but plenty of tropical flavour here. The finish is quite bitter which I expect from a great IPA. All around a great and unique IPA.
